00:30:51.930 --> 00:30:56.630
whose sexuality is so subtle at first its
literally in the background, out of focus.

401
00:30:56.630 --> 00:30:59.880
Early on in the film you’re not even likely
to notice the knowing looks they give each

402
00:30:59.880 --> 00:31:05.000
other, or even notice them spooning in the
back of a scene. But then BAM, they’re kidnapped

403
00:31:05.000 --> 00:31:09.290
and their lives are seemingly in danger so
they declare their literally undying love

404
00:31:09.290 --> 00:31:38.790
for one another. And goddammit it works. This
crazy, over the top action movie that would

405
00:31:38.790 --> 00:31:44.490
make some of the Fast and Furious movies look
subtle has, hands down, the best gay representation

406
00:31:44.490 --> 00:31:48.660
I’ve ever seen in a Hollywood movie. The
gays don’t die. They’re not depressed

407
00:31:48.660 --> 00:31:53.590
about being gay. Nobody wants to kill them
for being gay. It’s just… a thing they

408
00:31:53.590 --> 00:31:57.770
are. Something that has, really, nothing to
do with the plot. They could have been straight

409
00:31:57.770 --> 00:32:03.071
buds but, instead, they’re gay. They just
happen to be gay. And it is perfect. Unlike

410
00:32:03.071 --> 00:32:07.070
most gay characters they survive to the end
and will be in the sequel, which Netflix green-lit

411
00:32:07.070 --> 00:32:12.400
earlier this year. The movie was a huge success
for Netflix and other than gay media, almost

412
00:32:12.400 --> 00:32:18.210
nobody mentioned Joe and Nicky. Why? Because
Netflix didn’t put out a press release declaring

413
00:32:18.210 --> 00:32:21.930
“WE HAVE A GAY! TWO OF EM!”

414
00:32:21.930 --> 00:32:26.210
They just let the gays exist like they would
any straight character. They were just there.

415
00:32:26.210 --> 00:32:31.060
Their queerness completely incidental to the
plot, just like every other characters straightness.

416
00:32:31.060 --> 00:32:35.610
I was so shocked by this that I barely knew
what to think when I watched it. An action

417
00:32:35.610 --> 00:32:41.090
movie with gay characters. An action movie
with gay heroes? An action movie with gay

418
00:32:41.090 --> 00:32:42.650
heroes who don’t die?

419
00:32:42.650 --> 00:32:47.000
WHAT IS THIS? Opposite land?! Did the pandemic
cause a new reality to open up?

420
00:32:47.000 --> 00:32:52.680
Sadly, no. No new reality, just a single ripple
in spacetime that felt a bit different. Not

421
00:32:52.680 --> 00:32:58.110
a whole lot of incidentally gay characters
popping up in action movies since then. But

422
00:32:58.110 --> 00:33:00.180
one did come out just before it:

423
00:33:00.180 --> 00:33:06.820
The Birds of Prey and the Fabulous Emancipation
